Control Name: 3.9 Ensure no HTTPS or SSL proxy load balancers permit SSL policies with weak cipher suites
Control Statement: Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) policies determine what port Transport Layer Security (TLS) features clients are permitted to use when connecting to load balancers.
